<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective, 
<taxonomicName box="[651,743,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Houghia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifera">
<emphasis box="[651,743,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">aurifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “gold-bearing”, in reference to the bright golden tomentosity on the fronto-orbital plate and parafacial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
